2008-12-01  Alan D. Salewski  <asalewski@signatureinfo.com>

	* configure.ac
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): added check for IO::File
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): added check for IO::Handle
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): added check for IO::Scalar
	* NEWS: Noted new configure-time check for IO::Scalar

2008-11-26  Rob Lauer         <Rlauer@signatureinfo.com>

	* minor changes (see NEWS)

2008-11-25  Rob Lauer         <Rlauer@signatureinfo.com>

        * Don't expect a list of changes like Al has below ;-) but I'll do
	  my best...

        * re-organized (read deleted) some files to support the now
	  formulated Bedrock 2.0 plan of separating core Bedrock server
	  installation and virtual host creation.  To that end, the
	  directories:

          - examples
          - bedrock-works/src/main/bedrock/roc

	  Have been stripped of their files and instead directories:

	  src/main/bedrock/htdocs
	  src/main/bedrock/css
	  src/main/bedrock/pebbles
	  src/main/bedrock/img

	  ...have been created that contain resources that are installed into
	  ${PREFIX}/share/bedrock that will be used by the:

	    'bedrock-site-template'

	  ...project to create virtual host sites that are Bedrock 2.0
	  enabled.


2008-03-11  Alan D. Salewski  <ASalewski@signatureinfo.com>

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in
	(--perl5-include): new optional command line option
	(@PERL5_EXTRA_INCLUDES): new global
	(maybe_create_apache_mod_perl_startup_dot_pl_file_or_die): Accepts
	  new PERL5_EXTRA_INCLUDE named param
	(POD): updated to reflect above addition

	* autotools/ads_PERL_MODULE.m4: Redirect Perl's stderr to
	  /dev/null when testing for an OPTIONAL module

	* configure.ac (ads_PERL_MODULE): make Hash::Util Perl module
	  optional at configure time. This was an uncommitted change from
	  related work done on 2008-03-04.

2008-03-06  Alan D. Salewski  <ASalewski@signatureinfo.com>

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in
	(maybe_create_apache_site_config_file_or_die): Alias /Bedrock/img
	  to the installed bedrock ${htdocsdir}/img directory instead to
	  the ${site_dir}/htdocs/img directory
	(maybe_create_apache_site_config_file_or_die): Fixed handling of
	  overwrite permissions; was sometimes writing an empty file, plus
	  other issues.
	(--apache-auth-realm=STRING): new name for the
	  --apache-auth-db-prompt=STRING option; the old name has been
	  removed. The new default value is "UNCONFIGURED". Man page POD
	  and '-h' help message have been updated to reflect these
	  changes.
	(maybe_copy_dist_bedrock_dot_cgi_or_die): ensure that newly copied
	  file is readable and executable by its user and group; previously
	  were only ensuring this for "other".

	Changes to allow the user to specify user and group ownership of
	/most/ created files:
	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in:
	(--owner=OWNER): new command line opt
	(--group=GROUP): new command line opt
	($TO_OWNER_NAME): new global var
	($TO_GROUP_NAME): new global var
	(__poor_mans_touch): new function, like touch(1) for Perl
	(__chown_chgrp_all): new function, enhanced wrapper for Perl's
	  'chown' function
	(__create_directories_or_die): now returns list of directories
	  actually created
	(__maybe_create_site_subdirs_or_die): likewise
	(__maybe_create_site_directory_or_die): now returns a boolean
	  indicating whether or not the site directory needed to be created
	(maybe_create_site_directory_tree_or_die): Now changes user and
	  group ownershipt of all newly created directories
	(__maybe_create_named_file_or_die): now returns a boolean
	  indicating whether or not the file named by the MAINFILE param
	  needed to be created
	(maybe_create_tagx_dot_xml_or_die): now changes the user and group
	  ownership of the tagx.xml file, iff the file was newly created.
	(maybe_create_tagx_apps_dot_xml_or_die): likewise, but for the
	  tagx_apps.xml file
	(maybe_create_index_dot_rock_or_die): likewise, but for the
	  $sitedr/htdocs/index.rock file
	(maybe_create_admin_index_dot_rock_or_die): likewise, but for the
	  $sitedr/htdocs/admin/index.rock file
	(maybe_copy_dist_error_dot_rock_or_die): likewise, but for the
	  $sitedir/htdocs/error.rock file
	(maybe_create_apache_mod_perl_startup_dot_pl_file_or_die):
	  likewise, but for the apache site's mod_perl startup.pl-style file
	(maybe_copy_dist_bedrock_dot_cgi_or_die): now changes the user and
	  group ownership of the $sitedir/cgi-bin/bedrock.cgi file, iff
	  the file did not exist previously and needed to be copied from
	  the installed Bedrock distribution.
	(POD): The above features are fully documented in the program's
	  man page pod

	* configure.ac (AC_CONFIG_FILES): Added to list:
	  src/main/resources/htdocs/img/Makefile
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/error.rock (bedbug.jpg): prefix
	  '/Bedrock/' to img ref path
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/Makefile.am (SUBDIRS): Added 'img' to list
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/img/Makefile.am: new file
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/img/bedbug.jpg: new file (from bedrock 1.6.4 tarball)
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/img/bedrock.jpg: new file (from bedrock 1.6.4 tarball)
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/img/br_lcap.gif: new file (from bedrock 1.6.4 tarball)
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/img/br_rcap.gif: new file (from bedrock 1.6.4 tarball)
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/img/one.gif: new file (from bedrock 1.6.4 tarball)

2008-03-05  Alan D. Salewski  <ASalewski@signatureinfo.com>

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in: Doc fix
	(maybe_create_apache_site_config_file_or_die): Commented out
	  Apache site config 'ErrorDocument' directive that specified a
	  Bedrock-specific HTTP 401 document

2008-03-04  Alan D. Salewski  <ASalewski@signatureinfo.com>

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in
	(Hash::Util::lock_hash): Change for compatibility with Perl
	  pre-5.8.x; use of Hash::Util module is now optional, and
	  dependent on whether or not the module is installed.
	* README: updated docs to reflect the fact that Perl 5.8.x is no
	  longer required

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in
	(maybe_copy_dist_error_dot_rock_or_die): Copy 'error.rock', not
	  'index.rock', from the Bedrock distribution

	* examples/cli/bedrock-create-site-example.com: new file

	* configure.ac: 
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for Carp
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for Cwd
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for Fcntl
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for File::Basename
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for File::Copy
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for File::Path
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for File::Spec::Functions
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for Getopt::Long
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for Hash::Util
	(ads_PERL_MODULE): new check for Term::ReadKey

	* README: Doc update

	* NEWS: Doc update

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in
	(__maybe_create_named_file_or_die):
	- New function name (was formerly __maybe_create_named_index_dot_rock_file_or_die)
	- Refactored to allow for more general application (for use in
	  creating tagx.xml and tagx_apps.xml)
	- Refactored to use named params
	- Checking/creation of symlinks is now optional
	(--overwrite-tagx-dot-xml): new optional command line opt
	(--nooverwrite-tagx-dot-xml): new optional command line opt
	(--overwrite-tagx-apps-dot-xml): new optional command line opt
	(--nooverwrite-tagx-apps-dot-xml): new optional command line opt
	($DO_OVERWRITE_TAGX_DOT_XML): new "overwrite flag
	($DO_OVERWRITE_TAGX_APPS_DOT_XML): new "overwrite flag
	(maybe_create_tagx_dot_xml_or_die): new function
	(maybe_create_tagx_apps_dot_xml_or_die): new function
	($BEDROCK_DIST_PEBBLES_DIR): new var filtered in at build time
	(POD): Cleaned up existing and fleshed out bedrock-create-site(1) man page

	* configure.ac (pebblesdir): New AC_SUBST application
	* src/main/bedrock/pebbles/Makefile.am (pebblesdir): Moved
	  definition to top-level configure.ac file

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in (symlink): Added $! to
	  die messages thrown from all failed symlink() invocations

2008-03-03  Alan D. Salewski  <ASalewski@signatureinfo.com>

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in
	(with_changed_directory): new utility function. Used to update all
	  invocations of symlink() to create relative symlinks.

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in
	(--overwrite-admin-index-dot-roc): new optional command line opt
	(--nooverwrite-admin-index-dot-roc): new optional command line opt
	(--overwrite-admin-index-dot-rock): new optional command line opt
	(--nooverwrite-admin-index-dot-rock): new optional command line opt
	($DO_OVERWRITE_ADMIN_INDEX_DOT_ROC):  new "overwrite" flag
	($DO_OVERWRITE_ADMIN_INDEX_DOT_ROCK): new "overwrite" flag
	(__maybe_create_index_dot_rock_or_die): new parameterized function
	  that is a generalization of the old
	  'maybe_create_index_dot_rock_or_die()' function.
	(__maybe_create_named_index_dot_rock_file_or_die): new specialized content
	  producing worker func
	(maybe_create_index_dot_rock_or_die): changed to invoke above
	  parameterized worker func
	(maybe_create_admin_index_dot_rock_or_die): new func; also invokes
	  the above parameterized worker func


	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in
	(maybe_create_apache_mod_perl_startup_dot_pl_file_or_die): new function
	(--apache-mod-perl-startup=FILE): new required command line opt
	(--overwrite-apache-mod-perl-startup): new optional command line opt
	(--nooverwrite-apache-mod-perl-startup): new optional command line opt
	($BEDROCK_DIST_DATA_DIR): filter in a build time
	(SEE ALSO): /usr/sbin/a2ensite
	(SEE ALSO): /usr/sbin/a2dissite

	Renamed 'error.roc' to 'error.rock':
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/error.roc:  removed file
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/error.rock: added file
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/Makefile.am
	(dist_htdocs_DATA): Changed 'error.roc' reference to 'error.rock'
	(install-data-hook): New automake augmentation target that creates
	  an 'error.roc' symlink to our installed 'error.rock' file

	* src/main/perl/bin/bedrock-create-site.in
	(maybe_copy_dist_error_dot_rock_or_die): new function
	(--overwrite-error-dot-roc): new command line opt
	(--nooverwrite-error-dot-roc): new command line opt
	(--overwrite-error-dot-rock): new command line opt
	(--nooverwrite-error-dot-rock): new command line opt
	(maybe_copy_dist_bedrock_dot_cgi_or_die): new function
	(--overwrite-bedrock-dot-cgi): new command line opt
	(--nooverwrite-bedrock-dot-cgi): new command line opt
	- Doc updates for all of the above
	($BEDROCK_DIST_CGIBIN_DIR): filter in at build time
	($BEDROCK_DIST_HTDOCS_DIR): filter in at build time

	* src/main/perl/bin/Makefile.am (install-exec-hook): Invoke 'rm -f
	  foo' in front of '$(LN_S) file foo' to allow multiple invocations
	  of 'make install' to work.

	* configure.ac (cgibindir): New AC_SUBST application
	* src/main/perl/cgi-bin/Makefile.am (cgibindir): Moved definition
	  to top-level configure.ac file

	* configure.ac (htdocsdir): New AC_SUBST application
	* src/main/resources/htdocs/Makefile.am (htdocsdir): Moved
	  definition to top-level configure.ac file

	* src/main/resources/Makefile.am (bedrock-perl5-inc-begin-block.snippet):
	  file is now in the 'data_DATA' list rather than the
	  'noinst_DATA' list to cause it to be installed (for consumption
	  by external tools, etc.)

